               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist in Text II; names of other characters like Gäbrǝʾel (fols. 5ra, 45va, 46ra), Yoḥannǝs (fols. 5ra, 12va), Mikaʾel (fols. 13va, 44rb, 45va, 46ra); elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Several groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1b, I-2, I-4 (alternating with black lines); several groups of lines in the incipit of Text I-3 (alternating with black lines); two initial lines of Texts I-1a and its sections; two initial lines of sections of Texts I-1b, II and III und their section numbers; first one or two words of sections of Text I-2 and of each strophe of Text I-5.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam Mariham ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (fol. 13ra) (cp. ChRep no. 373)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam dǝngǝl ʾǝmmä mädḫǝn wä-ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (fol. 13ra-vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Texts I-1b, II and III are numbered (the numeration continues throughout these texts).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>One miracle of Text I-1b (numbered as 28) is followed by a hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam dǝngǝl wälättä ʾAron liqä kahǝnät... "O my Lady, Virgin Mary, daughter of Aaron the High Priest…" (fol. 42va)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 19 strophes which are strophes 1-10 (fols. 17va-24va), 12-14 (fols. 29va-31rb), 24-27 (fol. 36rb-40rb) and 29-30 (42va, 44ra) according to GrohHymn pp. 336-51.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="119rb"/>Fol. 119rb: ይትባረክ: እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ በዳኅና፡ ወምስለ፡ ጸሐፊሁ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ወአባሲ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም። ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ ወአሜን፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን። ተፈጸመ፡ በ፳: ፬ጥቅምት፡ በጊዜ፡ ፫ሰዓት፡ ዘረቡዕ።<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colophon mentiones the name of the scribe Gäbrä Maryam. The writing was completed on 24 Ṭǝqǝmt, in the third hour, on Wednesday.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
